TITLE: Implementing Async Loader with Promise Returns in React Router
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create a loader function that returns both immediate critical data and deferred non-critical data using promises. The loader awaits critical data while passing through the non-critical data promise.
SOURCE: https://github.com/remix-run/react-router/blob/main/docs/how-to/suspense.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import type { Route } from "./+types/my-route";

export async function loader({}: Route.LoaderArgs) {
  // note this is NOT awaited
  let nonCriticalData = new Promise((res) =>
    setTimeout(() => res("non-critical"), 5000)
  );

  let criticalData = await new Promise((res) =>
    setTimeout(() => res("critical"), 300)
  );

  return { nonCriticalData, criticalData };
}
```

