TITLE: Server-Side Redirect Middleware (TSX)
DESCRIPTION: This TSX snippet demonstrates a server-side middleware function that checks for 404 errors and attempts to redirect using CMS data. It exemplifies how to handle 404 status codes and perform redirects based on custom logic.  It showcases error handling and CMS integration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/remix-run/react-router/blob/main/packages/react-router/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
const redirects: Route.unstable_MiddlewareFunction = async ({
  request,
  next,
}) => {
  // attempt to handle the request
  let res = await next();

  // if it's a 404, check the CMS for a redirect, do it last
  // because it's expensive
  if (res.status === 404) {
    let cmsRedirect = await checkCMSRedirects(request.url);
    if (cmsRedirect) {
      throw redirect(cmsRedirect, 302);
    }
  }

  return res;
};
```

