TITLE: Server-Side Authentication Middleware (TSX)
DESCRIPTION: This TSX snippet showcases a server-side authentication middleware function in React Router. It checks for a user session and redirects to the login page if the user is not authenticated. It illustrates how to short-circuit the remaining processing using a `redirect`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/remix-run/react-router/blob/main/packages/react-router/CHANGELOG.md#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import { sessionContext } from "../context";
const serverAuth: Route.unstable_MiddlewareFunction = (
  { request, params, context },
  next
) => {
  let session = context.get(sessionContext);
  let user = session.get("user");
  if (!user) {
    session.set("returnTo", request.url);
    throw redirect("/login", 302);
  }
};
```

